        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 12:53PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 1253 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
South Lake Tahoe, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, heavy rain and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
South Lake Tahoe, Meyers, Kingsbury, South Lake Tahoe Airport, Fallen
Leaf Campground, Luther Pass, and Stateline.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
